post.description:
Returns the previously saved report.

Authentication

A public report is accessible by anyone, a private one is only accessible by the report's owner or workspace admin. If the criteria aren't met it returns 403 status code.

Parameters

The report can be executed without parameters, and in this case the saved or default parameters will be used.

parameters.description: Starting date in the format YYYY-MM-DD
parameters.name: start_date

parameters.description: Unix timestamp(UTC) or null for proper pagination. This parameter only works in Detailed and Summary reports.
parameters.name: first_timestamp

parameters.description: End date in the format YYYY-MM-DD. This parameter only works in Detailed and Summary reports.
parameters.name: end_date

parameters.description: How the rounding is done: 1 is rounding up, -1 down, 0 for no rounding.
parameters.name: rounding

parameters.description: If it is grouped or not. This parameter only works for Detailed report.
parameters.name: grouped

parameters.description: Criteria to group by. This parameter only works for Summary report.
parameters.name: grouping

parameters.description: Criteria to subgroup. This parameter only works for Summary report.
parameters.name: sub_grouping

client_ids.description: Client IDs, optional, filtering attribute. To filter records with no clients, use [null].

end_date.description: End date, example time.DateOnly. Should be greater than Start date.

granularity.description: Totals granularity, optional, overrides resolution values. Possible values: day, week and month.

grouped.description: Whether time entries should be grouped, optional, default false.

max_duration_seconds.description: Max duration seconds, optional, filtering attribute. Time Audit only, should be greater than MinDurationSeconds.

min_duration_seconds.description: Min duration seconds, optional, filtering attribute. Time Audit only, should be less than MaxDurationSeconds.

project_ids.description: Project IDs, optional, filtering attribute. To filter records with no projects, use [null].

resolution.description: Graph resolution, optional. Allow clients to explicitly request a resolution.

rounding.description: Whether time should be rounded, optional, default from user preferences.

rounding_minutes.description: Rounding minutes value, optional, default from user preferences. Should be 0, 1, 5, 6, 10, 12, 15, 30, 60 or 240.

start_date.description: Start date, example time.DateOnly. Should be less than End date.

tag_ids.description: Tag IDs, optional, filtering attribute. To filter records with no tags, use [null].

task_ids.description: Task IDs, optional, filtering attribute. To filter records with no tasks, use [null].

withInlineRates.description: Whether results should be returned in line, optional, default false.

with_graph.description: Whether Graph information should be loaded, optional,  default false.

billable.description: Whether the time entry is set as billable, optional, premium feature.

calculate.description: Calculate option, optional. Can be by time or amounts.

client_ids.description: Client IDs, optional, filtering attribute. To filter records with no clients, use [null].

date_format.description: Date format, optional, default "MM/DD/YYYY". Can be "MM/DD/YYYY", "DD-MM-YYYY", "MM-DD-YYYY", "YYYY-MM-DD", "DD/MM/YYYY" or "DD.MM.YYYY".

duration_format.description: Duration format, optional, default "classic". Can be "classic", "decimal" or "improved".

end_date.description: End date, example time.DateOnly. Should be greater than Start date.

group_by_task.description: GroupByTask tells the weekly report to return the data grouped by all the usual groups plus planned task.

max_duration_seconds.description: Max duration seconds, optional, filtering attribute. Time Audit only, should be greater than MinDurationSeconds.

min_duration_seconds.description: Min duration seconds, optional, filtering attribute. Time Audit only, should be less than MaxDurationSeconds.

project_ids.description: Project IDs, optional, filtering attribute. To filter records with no projects, use [null].

rounding.description: Whether time should be rounded, optional, default from user preferences.

rounding_minutes.description: Rounding minutes value, optional, default from user preferences. Should be 0, 1, 5, 6, 10, 12, 15, 30, 60 or 240.

start_date.description: Start date, example time.DateOnly. Should be less than End date.

tag_ids.description: Tag IDs, optional, filtering attribute. To filter records with no tags, use [null].

task_ids.description: Task IDs, optional, filtering attribute. To filter records with no tasks, use [null].
